com.zendesk.sdk.ui

Class KeyboardSearchListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.zendesk.sdk.ui.KeyboardSearchListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NoCopySpan, TextWatcher, View.OnKeyListener, TextView.OnEditorActionListener

    public class KeyboardSearchListener
extends Object
implements View.OnKeyListener, TextView.OnEditorActionListener, TextWatcher
    This class implements Listeners for searching for both software and hardware keyboards. It then provides a single KeyboardSearchListener.Searchable interface to receive search request events on.

    For hardware keyboards we listen for action KeyEvent.ACTION_DOWN with one of the following keycodes:

    • KeyEvent.KEYCODE_DPAD_CENTER
    • KeyEvent.KEYCODE_ENTER

    For software keyboards we listen for the user hitting the enter / search key on their IME. This can be set up in the TextView (or subclass like EditText) that has been specified with the following options: 

             android:imeOptions: actionSearch
         android:inputType:  text
